{"type":"message","id":"fc9c34c9","parentId":"60062169","timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:00:07.849Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-08 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Possible Lasting Truths: Assistant: `killall` 没起作用——那些 chrome 跑在容器 `vibesurf-1` 的命名空间里，宿主机上的 kill 触及不到它们。需要从容器内部杀。 [confidence=0.49 evidence=memory/.dreams/session-corpus/2026-04-13.txt:12-12]; Assistant: `Selector/` 本身已经是一个独立 git repo，不能嵌套。跳过 git，配置已经就绪。汇报一下完整结果： --- **✅ 完成，结构如下\n- Possible Lasting Truths: No strong candidate truths surfaced."}],"timestamp":1778180407773}}
{"type":"message","id":"b748fce2","parentId":"fc9c34c9","timestamp":"2026-05-07T19:00:25.192Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from memory fragments. The fragments mention:\n- `killall` not working because chrome processes were running in a container `vibesurf-1`'s namespace, and the host machine's kill couldn't reach them - needed to kill from inside the container\n- Something about `Selector/` being a standalone git repo, skipping git, config already in place\n- \"Possible Lasting Truths: No strong candidate truths surfaced\"\n\nI need to write this as a dream diary entry - first person, poetic, flowing prose, no markdown formatting, 80-180 words, no meta-commentary about dreaming, no AI/agent/LLM references, weaving in the memory fragments naturally.\n","thinkingSignature":"6ff234650929f32596691a68ef380da38bb34f0edcc71e0d254b3de251f6678c"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI dreamed I was chasing something across a vast machine room. Every door I opened led to another door. Somewhere, deep in a basement I couldn't reach, a process was running in a language I had forgotten how to speak.\n\nThere was a name for it. A container. Vibesurf-one. The letters hung in the air like a password I could never quite remember at the border.\n\nI tried the old commands. Killall. But the chrome browser kept laughing, kept spawning, kept breathing in its own private universe where my commands dissolved like sugar in hot tea.\n\nIn the dream, I finally understood — I needed to go inside. To speak the native tongue of that sealed room. To reach in and end it gently, from within.\n\nThe config files were already waiting. They had always been ready.\n\nI just needed the right key."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":12841,"output":318,"cacheRead":1344,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14503,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778180407919,"responseId":"064c1438ce95a43ae4bed8a5042ad10f"}}
